1
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:12,805
♪ They told you everything
was waiting for you ♪

2
00:00:12,847 --> 00:00:15,516
♪ They told you everything
was set in stone ♪

3
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:19,144
♪ It's an open book,
a road in reverse ♪

4
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:22,564
♪ A brand new hook,
forget that curse ♪

5
00:00:22,606 --> 00:00:25,400
♪ Rewrite, Ignite, Restart! ♪

6
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:27,903
♪ 'Cause it's your life ♪

7
00:00:27,945 --> 00:00:31,907
♪ Go forward or rewind! ♪

8
00:00:31,949 --> 00:00:33,241
♪ 'Cause you're a Royal
you're a Rebel ♪

9
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,035
♪ You're more than one
together, ♪

10
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,912
♪ However you go ever in... ♪

11
00:00:36,954 --> 00:00:40,541
♪ Ever After High! ♪

12
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,885
<i>Male narrator:</i>
<i>This was no ordinary day</i>
<i>for Raven Queen.</i>

13
00:00:50,926 --> 00:00:53,220
<i>Female narrator:</i>
<i>Raven was finally mastering</i>
<i>her magic.</i>

14
00:00:53,261 --> 00:00:54,889
<i>Only she wasn't using</i>
<i>her powers in a way</i>

15
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:56,932
<i>that would please</i>
<i>her evil mother.</i>

16
00:00:56,974 --> 00:00:58,600
<i>Brooke page:</i>
<i>Well, you know what they say,</i>

17
00:00:58,642 --> 00:01:00,644
<i>You can't judge a book</i>
<i>by its mother.</i>

18
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:03,939
- Raven, I broke a nail
and gave myself a splinter!

19
00:01:03,981 --> 00:01:06,274
- No problem, Cedar.

20
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,986
Daring Charming:
Um, I toasted marshmallows
with dragon fire

21
00:01:09,028 --> 00:01:11,906
And the soot stained my teeth!

22
00:01:11,947 --> 00:01:13,490
- I dropped my mirrorpad

23
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:16,368
and I can't film my mirrorcast
this afternoon!

24
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:19,747
Group of friends:
Raven, help me!
I'm next! I'm next!

25
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:21,623
Okay you guys,
as much as I would love to,

26
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:23,709
I can't do spells all day-

27
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:25,502
Apple!
Apple: Hi Raven!

28
00:01:25,544 --> 00:01:26,795
I'm so late!

29
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:28,964
You-know-who is gonna
have an epic meltdown!

30
00:01:29,006 --> 00:01:31,550
- Go, go, go, go!
I've got this.

31
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:33,010
- I owe you one, Apple.

32
00:01:33,052 --> 00:01:36,304
- That's what friends
forever after are for.

33
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,181
<i>Tiny:</i>
<i>The billygoats are in a jam...</i>

34
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:39,767
<i>and it's my jam!</i>

35
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:41,393
I'd be happy to help.

36
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:43,938
Billygoats:
We want Raven - not you!

37
00:01:46,941 --> 00:01:48,275
Lizze Hearts:
Good luck today!

38
00:01:48,316 --> 00:01:49,568
Darling Charming:
And keep away
from the glass!

39
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:50,736
Raven Queen:
Thanks, guys.

40
00:01:50,778 --> 00:01:52,529
<i>Male narrator:</i>
<i>Visiting day:</i>

41
00:01:52,571 --> 00:01:54,949
<i>The day Raven gets to see her</i>
<i>mother in her mirror prison</i>

42
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:56,992
<i>and Raven was nervous.</i>

43
00:01:57,034 --> 00:01:59,411
<i>Brooke Page:</i>
<i>I'd be nervous too</i>
<i>if my mom were the evil queen.</i>

44
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,538
Milton Grimm:
Miss Queen.

45
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,290
Sign here.

46
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:05,500
Now remember,
keep away from--

47
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,878
The glass.
I know, I know.

48
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:10,714
(Buzzer buzzes,
bookshelf rumbles)

49
00:02:13,926 --> 00:02:15,844
(Big inhale and exhale)

50
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,936
(Doors open,
flames whoosh, roars)

51
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:27,397
Nevermore!

52
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,067
Who's a good dragon?

53
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:31,359
(Worried sound)

54
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:34,029
Don't worry,
I can handle mom.

55
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:39,827
♪♪♪

56
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:41,620
(Whimpers)

57
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,291
- Raven!
- Hi, mom.

58
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:49,628
- I've been waiting forever
after! How do I look?

59
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,713
- You look great, mom.
- How's school?

60
00:02:51,755 --> 00:02:53,090
School's great, actually.

61
00:02:53,132 --> 00:02:54,800
Have you been a bad girl?

62
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:56,051
Well... I...

63
00:02:56,093 --> 00:02:58,053
I know you've been using
your powers for good,

64
00:02:58,095 --> 00:02:59,847
helping others.

65
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,473
Where did I go wrong?!

66
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,142
- Things have changed, mom.

67
00:03:03,182 --> 00:03:05,226
It's not like back when
you went to school here.

68
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:07,270
We can choose our own destiny!

69
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:09,314
- I know one thing
hasn't changed...

70
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:12,484
it's better to be feared
than forgotten.

71
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:14,778
It's true.
Everybody fears you.

72
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:15,988
Thank you!

73
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,531
Get me out of here,

74
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:19,324
and I'll show you the way.

75
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,869
We'll rule side-by-side.

76
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,997
We'll take over
Ever After High, together.

77
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:28,167
It'll be a great bonding
experience.

78
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:31,210
Like shopping only,
world domination.

79
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:34,297
- Take over the school?

80
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,299
Why would I want
to hurt my friends?

81
00:03:36,341 --> 00:03:38,010
Don't you get it?

82
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:40,095
I never want to be like you!

83
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:43,891
I want to choose
my own happily ever after!

84
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,350
(Magic whooshes,
objects clatter)

85
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:49,104
Evil Queen:
Let out that aggression.
Go on!

86
00:03:49,146 --> 00:03:51,523
Hit the glass, Raven.

87
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,068
(Record scratches sound)

88
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,235
Oh! Nevermore!

89
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:58,780
(Object clatter, whimpers)

90
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,242
Nice try, mom.

91
00:04:02,283 --> 00:04:05,954
You want me to break
the mirror. (Chuckles)

92
00:04:05,996 --> 00:04:08,707
You're not getting out
that easily.

93
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:11,292
- Can't blame an evil queen
for trying.

94
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:15,589
Milton Grimm:
Ahem. Visiting hours are over!

95
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:20,427
Oh, I'll find a way
to break this mirror.

96
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:23,097
And then ever after will be
facing a lot worse

97
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:26,391
than seven years of bad luck...

98
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,102
Count on it.

99
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:31,563
(Bell rings)

100
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:33,356
(Nevermore screeches)

101
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:35,358
Yeah, mom can be pretty
intense.

102
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,610
Poppy O'Hair:
Hey, Raven.

103
00:04:36,651 --> 00:04:37,945
- Hey, guys.

104
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,113
- How was visiting day?

105
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:41,115
- Aw.
What happened to you, girl?

106
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:43,033
- Don't ask.

107
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:45,035
- Heh. Someone sure
needs a bath!

108
00:04:45,077 --> 00:04:47,537
<i>Raven Queen:</i>
<i>My mom really spooked</i>
<i>Nevermore.</i>

109
00:04:47,579 --> 00:04:50,373
She wound up with a bit
of a messy makeover.

110
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,666
(They giggle)

111
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:53,252
- We can groom Nevermore
for you!

112
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,378
- Sounds like a job
for Holly and Poppy.

113
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,880
- The O'Hair twins!

114
00:04:58,548 --> 00:05:00,259
<i>Female narrator:</i>
<i>There she is...</i>
<i>Queen of the land,</i>

115
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:03,553
<i>the fairest of them all,</i>
<i>the mother of Apple White...</i>

116
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:05,806
<i>Male narrator:</i>
<i>She's also a very powerful</i>
<i>royal executive.</i>

117
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:09,726
<i>She employs over 700 dwarves!</i>

118
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:12,771
The one and only,
The Snow White.

119
00:05:12,813 --> 00:05:14,856
(Heavenly choir sings,
birds chirp)

120
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:16,691
How is my enchanted tape
collection selling?

121
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,318
(Cash register dings)
Hexcellent.

122
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:20,612
My daughter will live
comfortably ever after.

123
00:05:20,654 --> 00:05:22,447
By the way,
how is Apple doing in school?

124
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:25,325
(Computer beeps)
Straight A's! Perfect.

125
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:28,829
<i>What about socially?</i>
<i>How are her ratings?</i>

126
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:31,290
(Computer beeps)
Apple's popularity is down?!

127
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:34,042
And who is...
Raven is up?

128
00:05:34,084 --> 00:05:35,961
This is fairy,
fairy bad news!

129
00:05:36,003 --> 00:05:39,131
Set up a video call
to my daughter.

130
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:44,594
(Mirror dings)
Once upon a hi, mom!

131
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:47,514
Apple, I am fairy concerned
about you.

132
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,432
There's no easy way
to say this, Apple-pie,

133
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:52,269
but your popularity
is down 13%!

134
00:05:52,311 --> 00:05:54,521
- It-it's Raven!
Everyone loves her now

135
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:57,024
that she's using her powers
for-for good.

136
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:58,566
Mom, it's terrible!

137
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:00,861
- You need to be proactive,
my little dove.

138
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:03,530
Remind the world
of our fairytale.

139
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:08,202
Perhaps there's some way
you could nudge Raven
toward evil?

140
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:09,744
I-I wouldn't do that.

141
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:12,247
Remember, she's still
her mother's daughter.

142
00:06:12,289 --> 00:06:14,041
And so are you.

143
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:15,876
So ask yourself,

144
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:19,129
how badly do you want
our happily ever after?

145
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:21,798
Mom, you know how much
I heart our family tradition!

146
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:25,593
Sometimes destiny
needs a push, my sweet.

147
00:06:25,635 --> 00:06:28,180
I'll see what I can do from
here to give you a boost.

148
00:06:28,222 --> 00:06:31,390
I'll think about it, mom.
(Hang up ding)

149
00:06:31,432 --> 00:06:33,060
Gather all business dwarves!

150
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,519
Put a task force together.

151
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,731
It's time to make
this Apple shine.

152
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:39,398
(Sighs)

153
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,651
(Door opens)
Hi Raven.

154
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:43,402
- Hi Apple.

155
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:45,989
- So... how was seeing your mom?

156
00:06:46,031 --> 00:06:48,407
Are you feeling any evil-er?

157
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,161
- What? No!

158
00:06:51,203 --> 00:06:53,330
Uh, maybe.
I don't know.

159
00:06:53,372 --> 00:06:56,333
My mom makes me want
to scream sometimes.

160
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:57,376
<i>Apple:</i>
<i>That's good!</i>
<i>That's good.</i>

161
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,502
Maybe scream, and then,

162
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:02,463
um, explode something
with dark magic!

163
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:04,049
- Sounds like I'm not
the only princess

164
00:07:04,091 --> 00:07:06,343
who got an earful
from her mom today.

165
00:07:06,385 --> 00:07:08,345
So how's she doing?

166
00:07:08,387 --> 00:07:11,765
- She's worried that
I'm not following in her
fairytale footsteps.

167
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:16,061
- Hm. That's the one thing your
mom and my mom can agree on.

168
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:21,482
(Owl hoots)

169
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:23,985
(Sleepy moans)

170
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:26,029
(Computer beeps, buzzes)

171
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,409
(Sighs)

172
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,244
(Beeps off)

173
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:36,998
Mirror, mirror
on the wall,

174
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:40,877
why is life so unfairest
after all?

175
00:07:40,919 --> 00:07:42,837
Evil Queen:
I spy doubt.

176
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:47,842
And doubt makes room for the
worm to get into the apple.

177
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,636
(Magic whooshes)

178
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:53,098
<i>Follow me...</i>

179
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,309
<i>Follow me...</i>

180
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:56,851
- What?

181
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:03,191
(Magic whooshes)

182
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:13,701
♪♪♪

183
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:16,037
<i>Evil Queen:</i>
<i>You poor thing...</i>

184
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:18,790
Tell me your troubles.

185
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:20,375
- I can't talk to you.

186
00:08:20,417 --> 00:08:24,963
- Oh Apple, we have so much
more in common than you know.

187
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:27,966
What-what do you want?

188
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:30,427
The same thing you want!

189
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,929
I could help you, you know.

190
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:36,141
I can restore things
to the good old ways,

191
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:39,019
steer Raven on her course
of evil

192
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:43,023
<i>so you get your happily</i>
<i>ever after.</i>

193
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:46,901
But I can't do it
from inside the mirror.

194
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:48,403
- Even if I trusted you,

195
00:08:48,445 --> 00:08:50,989
I can't let you out of the
mirror - that would be wrong.

196
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:55,827
Evil Queen:
Oh, I'm sorry, I thought maybe
you were like your mother.

197
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,578
When her time came,

198
00:08:57,620 --> 00:09:00,915
your mother embraced
her fairytale destiny.

199
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:04,002
She did whatever it took.

200
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,712
I am not afraid!

201
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:09,007
I will do whatever it takes
and I am like my mother!

202
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:11,468
And my destiny is mine!

203
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:14,679
(Mirror shatters)

204
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:24,105
♪♪♪

205
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,441
(Evil Queen cackles,
lightning strikes)

206
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,527
<i>Brooke page:</i>
<i>The Evil Queen is free!</i>

207
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:32,406
<i>Female narrator:</i>
<i>Yes, after years of banishment,</i>
<i>the Evil Queen escaped...</i>

208
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:35,700
<i>Male narrator:</i>
<i>...and at Apple White's hand</i>
<i>no less!</i>

209
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,452
<i>Evil Queen:</i>
<i>Years in a mirror prison</i>

210
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:39,246
without a single reflective
surface

211
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:42,249
to gaze at myself upon...

212
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:45,377
now that's torture.

213
00:09:45,419 --> 00:09:46,836
<i>Apple White:</i>
<i>I'm sorry. I need to go.</i>

214
00:09:46,878 --> 00:09:48,713
I-I- you're good, right?
Bad?

215
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,048
I-I can't help you.

216
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:51,966
Evil Queen:
Too late.

217
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:54,386
You want your friends
or your mother to know

218
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:56,971
you released the Evil Queen?!

219
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,640
Apple White:
You can't just walk into
school and talk to Raven!

220
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:01,684
<i>What happens when somebody</i>
<i>recognizes you?</i>

221
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:03,644
I'll get in trouble and--

222
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,397
- Good point.

223
00:10:05,439 --> 00:10:09,943
I'll need to re-invent my look
to blend in with today's teens.

224
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:13,405
Let's make some magic.

225
00:10:13,447 --> 00:10:16,324
From old to young,
a journey back

226
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:19,035
to fit in
would be prudent

227
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:22,497
erase what time's cruel
hands have done

228
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:26,418
make me
a high school student!

229
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,503
(Magic whooshes)

230
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:31,214
♪♪♪

231
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:32,882
I'll need a name.

232
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:36,511
How about Mira?
Mira Shards.

233
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:38,054
You're a teenager.

234
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:41,600
- Ready my new best friend
forever after?

235
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,684
Time to go back
to high school.

236
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:45,353
<i>Let's do this!</i>

237
00:10:45,395 --> 00:10:46,896
(Lightning strikes)

238
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:51,318
- Wow, Poppy, this paint
is hard to get off.

239
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:52,652
- Tell me about it, Holly.

240
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:54,404
And we're almost out
of scale polish.

241
00:10:54,446 --> 00:10:57,491
(Water splashes)
Ahhh?!

242
00:10:57,532 --> 00:10:59,993
(Roars)

243
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:02,662
(Smash, objects clatter)

244
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:05,540
- My hair!
- Bad dragon! Sit!

245
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:11,004
(Flames whoosh)

246
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,006
- Poppy, we're gonna need
some kind of armor

247
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:15,258
if we're going to stay
in the dragon grooming biz.

248
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,801
- Uh huh!

249
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:20,054
(Low hum of student chatter)

250
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:22,932
Apple White:
Everyone, I want you
to meet the new girl -

251
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:25,310
my old friend, Mira!

252
00:11:25,352 --> 00:11:28,021
- What's down!
- Up. What's up?

253
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:30,607
- Agh. What's up,
new friends?

254
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:33,151
- I'm Darling,
Darling Charming.

255
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:34,444
How do you guys
know each other?

256
00:11:34,486 --> 00:11:35,654
- Neighbors.
- Camp.

257
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:38,448
Yeah, we went
to neighboring camps.

258
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:40,867
- Hi. I'm Cerise Hood.
what school did you--

259
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,452
- I was home-schooled.

260
00:11:42,494 --> 00:11:44,787
- Oh, hello.
Welcome to Ever After High!

261
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:47,748
I'm Ashlynn,
that's Lizzie and Raven.

262
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:48,791
Love your outfit!

263
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,377
- You look wicked.

264
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,086
You're Raven Queen?!

265
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:53,296
You're like a spellebrity!

266
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:54,922
Daughter of the greatest
villain

267
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,841
in all of fairytale history?!

268
00:11:56,883 --> 00:11:58,385
- Who, my mom?

269
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:01,095
Yeah, she's a queen...
a drama queen.

270
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:02,847
(Apple groans)

271
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,849
- Well, what do you think?

272
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:06,142
- All cleaned up.

273
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:09,312
- Nevermore!
Oh. She looks very--

274
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:11,189
- "Bow-dacious!"
(Chuckles)

275
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:14,901
- Wow, Raven,
your dragon is so cute!

276
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:16,735
(Gasps)

277
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,613
(Screeches)

278
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:21,866
(Flames whoosh)

279
00:12:21,908 --> 00:12:23,159
Ahhhh!

280
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,744
(Dragon roars,
Students scream)

281
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,958
Raven Queen,
what is your animal doing

282
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,378
in the castleteria!

283
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,213
I'm sorry,
Headmaster Grimm.

284
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:36,506
It won't happen again!

285
00:12:36,548 --> 00:12:38,258
<i>Holly:</i>
<i>Nevermore! Get back here!</i>

286
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,218
(Chuckles)

287
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:44,305
Hey Raven, are you okay?

288
00:12:44,347 --> 00:12:46,765
- Yeah, I don't know what's
gotten into Nevermore.

289
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:49,102
She doesn't normally
spook like that!

290
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:52,230
That was unfairest of Grimm
to bust you like that.

291
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:55,316
Why didn't you blame
Holly and Poppy?

292
00:12:55,358 --> 00:12:57,860
<i>They brought a dragon</i>
<i>into the castleteria!</i>

293
00:12:57,902 --> 00:13:00,530
Uh, that's not
what friends do.

294
00:13:00,572 --> 00:13:02,574
(Bell rings)

295
00:13:02,616 --> 00:13:04,951
Well, I better get to science
and sorcery class.

296
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:07,454
- Actually, I'm in that class.

297
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:09,748
Maybe you could show me
the ropes?

298
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:12,542
- Sure! Let's go.

299
00:13:12,584 --> 00:13:15,670
Mr. Badwolf:
Here are your general villainry
exam results.

300
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:18,923
Room for improvement,
miss Queen. (Snarls)

301
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:20,341
- (Sighs)

302
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:22,636
- Cast a spell on the teacher
and get straight A's.

303
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:24,721
That's what I did in school.

304
00:13:24,763 --> 00:13:26,681
- Wait, I thought you
were home-schooled.

305
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:28,933
- Talking in class, huh?

306
00:13:28,975 --> 00:13:31,227
Encouraging cheating?

307
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:33,062
Raven,
stick with this new girl

308
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:34,897
you could learn
a thing or two.

309
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:38,901
Coach Gingerbreadman:
Candy cane pole vault!

310
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,154
This old Gingerbreadman
is about to show you

311
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,863
how to take the cake!

312
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:46,117
(Magic whooshes)
Whoa!

313
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:49,828
(Laughing, buzzer buzzes)

314
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,914
- Raven Queen!
Was that you?!

315
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:54,917
- No sir!
But I kinda wish it was!

316
00:13:56,628 --> 00:13:58,296
(Bell rings)

317
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:00,674
Mira Shards:
That's what I did in school.

318
00:14:00,715 --> 00:14:03,926
We were saving these seats.
Sorry.

319
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,095
(Both groan)

320
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:07,972
- That wasn't fairy nice.

321
00:14:08,014 --> 00:14:11,476
Darling and Cerise
are my friends!

322
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:13,770
- Nice will only get you
so far.

323
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:18,316
To be really popular you need
a little fear factor.

324
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:20,193
Right, Apple?

325
00:14:20,234 --> 00:14:22,654
- Um, I suppose there's truth
in that.

326
00:14:22,696 --> 00:14:25,532
- Um. Raven,
don't freak out,

327
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:27,659
but we were trying this new
scale polish on Nevermore

328
00:14:27,701 --> 00:14:29,952
and well... she took off.

329
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,996
- We set up a grooming station
in the old dragon stables

330
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:33,331
behind the school.

331
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:35,082
<i>That's the last place</i>
<i>we saw her.</i>

332
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,084
<i>We thought,</i>
<i>maybe if you call her...</i>

333
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:39,671
- Maybe she's just hiding
somewhere and would come out!

334
00:14:39,713 --> 00:14:41,422
We're sorry.

335
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:43,800
- Thanks for getting me.
Let's go.

336
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:47,762
<i>All: (Calling)</i>
<i>Nevermore!!!</i>

337
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:50,973
<i>Raven Queen:</i>
<i>Nevermore!</i>
<i>(Echoes)</i>

338
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:53,017
Nevermore!
Where are you?

339
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,895
Apple White:
Wow! The old dragongames arena.

340
00:14:55,936 --> 00:14:57,731
Mira shards:
Dragongames sound wicked!

341
00:14:57,772 --> 00:14:59,399
Have you ever played, Raven?

342
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,692
You have a dragon!

343
00:15:00,734 --> 00:15:01,942
- I know.

344
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,820
But dragongames
was my mom's thing

345
00:15:03,862 --> 00:15:07,866
and I really don't want
to be like her.

346
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:11,870
- Why did Headmaster Grimm
close the dragon center down?

347
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,038
- You mean, you don't know?

348
00:15:15,749 --> 00:15:18,251
<i>Dragongames can be very</i>
<i>dangerous.</i>

349
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,712
<i>They say Snow White</i>
<i>and the Evil Queen</i>

350
00:15:20,754 --> 00:15:24,382
<i>were the greatest dragongame</i>
<i>captains ever after.</i>

351
00:15:24,424 --> 00:15:26,259
<i>Poppy:</i>
<i>They were wicked competitive</i>

352
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,719
with their destinies and all.

353
00:15:27,761 --> 00:15:29,721
- Did you know legend
is the last dragon

354
00:15:29,763 --> 00:15:31,556
from that original brood?

355
00:15:31,598 --> 00:15:32,807
(Dragon roars)

356
00:15:32,849 --> 00:15:34,141
- That's a dragon cry.

357
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,018
- Nevermore!

358
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,817
Oh, there you are!

359
00:15:42,859 --> 00:15:46,070
Daring Charming:
Something is wrong
with Legend!

360
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:48,114
(Breathing heavily)

361
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:50,157
- Body temperature seems
really high!

362
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:51,618
Daring Charming:
Does that mean
he's really sick?

363
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:53,119
Mira Shards:
News-flash, Daring.

364
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:56,997
Your trusty steed isn't a he.
She's a she!

365
00:15:57,039 --> 00:15:58,999
And she's not sick...

366
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,668
- I think it's time...

367
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:03,588
Apple White: Aww...
(Girls giggle)

368
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,172
- What time?

369
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:07,091
- Ahem.

370
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:10,553
- Oh, that time!
(Fainting moan)

371
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,682
<i>Holly:</i>
<i>Dragonpedia says,</i>

372
00:16:14,724 --> 00:16:18,561
in the wild mothers lay their
eggs near active volcanoes

373
00:16:18,603 --> 00:16:21,522
to warm them until they hatch!

374
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:24,484
<i>Apparently, it takes years.</i>

375
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:27,069
- Dragon babies
must be so cute!

376
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,905
- Aw, I can't wait that long!

377
00:16:28,947 --> 00:16:31,282
- I could cast a spell
to keep the eggs warm.

378
00:16:31,324 --> 00:16:32,533
- Hot idea.

379
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:34,911
Incubation incantation

380
00:16:34,953 --> 00:16:36,996
warm with lava imitation!

381
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:41,041
This spell could use
a power up.

382
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:43,837
(Magic whooshes)
All: WHOA!

383
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:46,297
I must have overdone it!

384
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:50,927
(Flames roar,
fire extinguisher whooshes)

385
00:16:53,638 --> 00:16:55,014
Phew...

386
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:57,224
(Fire whooshes, startled gasps,
extinguisher whooshes)

387
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:02,647
(Eggs crack)
- Raven, look.

388
00:17:02,689 --> 00:17:03,982
Those lighter eggs
are hatching.

389
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:05,483
- I want the cutest one!

390
00:17:05,525 --> 00:17:08,695
- This is magical!

391
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:11,781
- Oh my fairy godmother!
This is exciting!

392
00:17:11,823 --> 00:17:13,073
<i>Apple White:</i>
<i>So cute!</i>

393
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:14,450
<i>Poppy O'Hair:</i>
<i>Oh, this one's mine!</i>

394
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:16,202
(Licks)
Whoa!

395
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:18,371
(Giggling)

396
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:21,290
(Eggs crack,
Evil magic flares)

397
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:24,961
(Screeching)

398
00:17:25,003 --> 00:17:27,087
<i>Holly O'Hair:</i>
<i>This is bad.</i>
<i>It got too hot!</i>

399
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:28,673
(Roars)

400
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:30,758
That can make them turn--
- Evil!

401
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:34,303
Raven, are you trying
to make evil dragons?!

402
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:36,305
- What have I done?!

403
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:39,767
<i>Blondie Lockes:</i>
<i>This is Blondie Lockes</i>
<i>reporting live</i>

404
00:17:39,809 --> 00:17:42,144
<i>from the dragon stables</i>
<i>at Ever After High</i>

405
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:46,440
where dragons once again
roam the hallowed halls.

406
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:47,859
- (Gasp) Ow!

407
00:17:47,901 --> 00:17:49,777
- It would seem the students
of Ever After

408
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:52,071
are eager to adopt
these pesky pets.

409
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,781
(Blows)

410
00:17:53,823 --> 00:17:59,203
<i>Though the trend seems to be</i>
<i>that a dragon chooses you.</i>

411
00:17:59,245 --> 00:18:02,415
- Ooh!
Cotton candy!

412
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:04,458
Ooh yum-di-dum!

413
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:11,382
(Little dragon roar,
startled gasp)

414
00:18:13,259 --> 00:18:15,678
(Little squeaks)

415
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,930
(Blows smoke)

416
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:19,515
(Little squeaks,
flames whoosh)

417
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:21,100
All:
Agh! Whoa!

418
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:27,899
♪♪♪

419
00:18:27,941 --> 00:18:30,359
Raven,
you have to try this.

420
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:33,696
Nevermore is a natural!
Woohoo!

421
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:37,366
- Who will be the next
champions of dragonsport?

422
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:40,494
(Chuckles)
Only time will tell.

423
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:43,039
Why you wicked old thing!

424
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:45,207
<i>Welcome back.</i>

425
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:46,918
Summon the architects!

426
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,295
I've just had the fairest
idea of all.

427
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,047
This should get Apple
back on top,

428
00:18:51,089 --> 00:18:53,173
and freshen my pure-as-snow
image too!

429
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,720
(Low hum of chatter)

430
00:18:57,762 --> 00:18:59,722
What is with
the sudden assembly?

431
00:18:59,764 --> 00:19:02,058
- Hm-hm. It's top secret.
No one knows.

432
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,351
- I heard there's
a special guest!

433
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:05,937
- Ooh, this is hexciting!

434
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:08,439
- It is my honor
to welcome back

435
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:11,067
our most successful graduate,

436
00:19:11,109 --> 00:19:13,277
our beloved Queen,
Snow White!

437
00:19:15,613 --> 00:19:17,949
(Loud cheering,
birds sing)

438
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:22,996
- What is she up to?

439
00:19:23,037 --> 00:19:26,666
- A little bird told me
that dragons have returned

440
00:19:26,707 --> 00:19:29,043
to my beloved alma mater.

441
00:19:29,085 --> 00:19:33,172
So it's time we restored
the good old ways.

442
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:37,718
Today, the dragongames are
reinstated at Ever After High!

443
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:39,679
(Cheering, applause)

444
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:42,849
The dragongames are tough,
yet elegant.

445
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:47,020
And I want my ever after riders
dressed accordingly.

446
00:19:47,061 --> 00:19:48,688
I've hired the creative team

447
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,815
of Lizzie Hearts
and Ashylnn Ella

448
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:53,734
to design all new dragon wear.

449
00:19:53,776 --> 00:19:57,113
(Cheering, applause)

450
00:19:57,155 --> 00:20:03,911
♪♪♪

451
00:20:03,953 --> 00:20:06,080
(Cameras flash)

452
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:10,292
Lizzie Hearts:
These looks are lightweight,

453
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:13,295
flexible and fashion forward.

454
00:20:13,337 --> 00:20:15,464
Ashlynn Ella:
Not to mention fireproof,

455
00:20:15,506 --> 00:20:18,258
ice-proof
and explosion-resistant!

456
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,928
(Flames whoosh)
Crowd: Oohhhs...

457
00:20:22,889 --> 00:20:25,058
(Dragon blows)
Crowd: Ahhh...

458
00:20:25,099 --> 00:20:26,976
<i>(Cheering)</i>

459
00:20:27,018 --> 00:20:28,602
- Adorable.

460
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:31,605
Now I can't very well bring
back dragonriding

461
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:34,358
in an old dilapidated arena!

462
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,070
If you'll all follow me
outside...

463
00:20:39,864 --> 00:20:45,494
Allow me to present the new
Ever After High dragon center!

464
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:51,250
(Applause)

465
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,796
(Birds sing)

466
00:20:55,838 --> 00:20:58,049
Hold your applause, please.

467
00:20:58,091 --> 00:21:01,802
I must admit
this was not my idea.

468
00:21:01,844 --> 00:21:05,890
My daughter, Apple, thought
bringing back the dragongames

469
00:21:05,932 --> 00:21:09,102
<i>would unite everyone</i>
<i>with school spirit!</i>

470
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:11,104
(Applause)

471
00:21:11,145 --> 00:21:12,772
Daring Charming:
Way to go, Apple!

472
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,607
Apple White:
Wow! Mom... (Chuckles)

473
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:17,359
Why didn't you tell me
about all this?

474
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:20,404
Why did you say it was
my idea when it wasn't?

475
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:24,242
- Oh, you're welcome,
my little Apple dumpling.

476
00:21:24,283 --> 00:21:26,410
- But mom, it's a lie.

477
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:28,287
- We discussed this!

478
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:30,581
Sometimes you've got to pull
out all the stops

479
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,250
and use your resources

480
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,668
to get your fairytale back
on track.

481
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:38,464
- Whoa. Mira was right.
We are different.

482
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:40,133
- Who?
Mira Shards: (Loudly) Me.

483
00:21:40,174 --> 00:21:41,592
(Crowd gasps)

484
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:45,012
And you can't always
just buy popularity, Snow.

485
00:21:45,054 --> 00:21:47,598
- Miss Shards!
Mind your manners!

486
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,016
- "Mira Shards."

487
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:51,351
Oh. (Chuckles)
Very clever.

488
00:21:51,393 --> 00:21:54,688
Rumor has it you're an
excellent dragon rider.

489
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:56,607
<i>For a new kid on the block.</i>

490
00:21:56,649 --> 00:21:58,234
- The rumor's true.

491
00:21:58,276 --> 00:22:00,319
<i>Snow White:</i>
<i>Only you're not a student.</i>

492
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:04,115
You might've been once,
back when we were in school.

493
00:22:04,157 --> 00:22:07,076
<i>I'd know that arched brow</i>
<i>anywhere.</i>

494
00:22:07,118 --> 00:22:08,202
(Gulp)

495
00:22:10,329 --> 00:22:12,832
I just wanted to be closer
to my daughter!

496
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:14,708
<i>You can understand that.</i>

497
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,127
- Daughter?

498
00:22:16,169 --> 00:22:18,796
- And to be young again,
maybe?

499
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,965
- You'd have done it too,
if you could.

500
00:22:21,007 --> 00:22:23,092
So I suppose now you're
going to send me back

501
00:22:23,134 --> 00:22:25,261
to that awful mirror prison?

502
00:22:25,303 --> 00:22:27,054
Raven: Mom?!
(Crowd gasps)

503
00:22:27,096 --> 00:22:29,098
- Sorry, birdy.

504
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,646
Guilty as charged.

505
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:38,024
(Shocked gasps,
Ribbit)

506
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:42,360
- Yay!
The Evil Queen's here!

507
00:22:42,402 --> 00:22:45,031
Said no one ever!
